	 <h4>(c) The top retweet analysis and the ratio of tweets to retweets</h4>
   <p> After my analysis of the "top10 twitters and retwitters", I found that the most influential twitter came from an article published by moneycontrolcm on Jan9. moneycontrolcm is a twitter that provides unique analysis for markets, companies and the economy. This article is a preview of an interview with Ather founder Tarun, which will focus on the battle for market share in the electric vehicle space and the industry's response to #Budget2023 expect.Even though it was only retweeted 10 times and only had 63 likes. But this tweet has 10.1k views. </P>
	 <p>I got a total of 3823 tweets, of which 1911 retweets, the ratio is around 50%.</p>
   <img src="img/Top tweet.png" class="uk-width-1-2@s">

   <h4>(d) The ratio of tweet/retweets came from the top 10 tweeters</h4>
	 <P>Top10 Twitters released a total of 494 tweets, of which 211 retweets, retweets/tweets is 42.7%.</P>

   <h4>(e) Sentiment analysis</h4>
	 <p>I analyzed tweets and retweets from top10 twitters that are more representative of the Cyber Security hashtag. Before sorting out these tweets and retweets, I did some data screening and cleaned up some daily usage. To my surprise, apart from the predictable words like "security" and "hacker", companies related to new energy such as "Cenn" and "Tesla" also often appear under the hashtags. At the same time, #EV and #CENN is often seen alongside #Cyber Security.</p>
   <img src="img/Sentiment analysis.png" class="uk-width-1-2@s">

	 <h4>(f) Demographic Analysis</h4>
	 <p>In my database, there are a total of 2495 twitters, and they come from 1169 different regions. Most of them are from "India", "Israel", "London", "United States", "Waterloo, Ontario Canada".</p>
   <!--Use datawrapper to make charts, and use JS to show them in html-->
	 <iframe title="[ Insert title here ]" aria-label="Map" id="datawrapper-chart-YzFYY" src="https://datawrapper.dwcdn.net/YzFYY/1/" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" style="border: none;" width="600" height="294" data-external="1"></iframe>
   <p>twitters from different regions are talking about different topics in #Cyber Security. After my analysis, twitters from India often discuss topics such as "EV" and "Hacker". Twitters from Israel frequently discuss the topics "intelligence" and "Threatintell" with both topics appearing more than 70 times. Netizens from London and US obviously pay more attention to "EV" related topics. To my surprise, Twitters in Canada are very focused on the topics of "Autoindustry" and "Automobileindustry", both appearing more than 20 times.</p>
